a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes f :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. f x = 2 * x powr 2 - 4 * x + 9"
shows  "2 * f 3 + 3 * f (-3) = 147"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Consider the function $f(x) = 2x^2 - 4x + 9$.  Evaluate $2f(3) + 3f(-3)$. The final Answer is 147
 ### Proof
 We have $f(3) = 2(3^2) - 4\cdot 3 + 9 = 18 - 12 + 9 = 15$ and $f(-3) = 2(-3)^2 - 4(-3) + 9 = 18 +12+9 = 39$.
 So, we have $2f(3)+3f(-3) = 2(15) + 3(39) = 30 + 117 = \boxed{147}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes f :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. f x = 2 * x powr 2 - 4 * x + 9"
shows  "2 * f 3 + 3 * f (-3) = 147"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
